genresAdvancedInfo.name: czech contemporary classical
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Czech contemporary classical music is a genre that includes music composed by Czech composers in the 20th and 21st centuries. This music is characterized by its experimentation with new sounds, structures, and techniques, and it often incorporates elements of electronic music, jazz, and rock.
